                <span class="nanny-section-label">What to include in the budget</span>
                <h2>Look beyond monthly salary alone</h2>
                <p>When families compare nanny cost Dubai options, they should consider the full arrangement. This may include monthly salary, accommodation if live-in, meals, transport, agreed rest days, annual leave expectations, overtime, travel support, insurance, and any local administrative or visa-related process considerations to verify separately. Trusted Household &amp; Childcare does not provide legal promises; families should confirm formal employment, sponsorship, and regulatory details with qualified local advisers or relevant authorities.</p>
                <p>The consultation conversation helps families avoid vague expectations. A candidate should understand the role before deciding whether it is suitable, and a family should understand what kind of profile they are requesting. Clear expectations support better introductions and reduce the risk of mismatch later.</p>
            </div>
